qx|A1,INTRODUCTION|
ht|B|FP|2|cs|1|cp|4|at|^-{          INTRODUCTION          }
^-|cp||CS||FP||at|^b@2
One of the most common defensive errors less experienced players make is to not train themselves to play second hand low smoothly and quickly. There are few exceptions to this rule. The main exception you should keep in mind is that it is ok to play second hand high to win the trick when it is the setting trick (or your side can cash the setting tricks). But other than that, if you always play second hand low smoothly, it will gain you far more tricks than it will lose you. So it is very important that you train yourself to smoothly duck when you are second hand to a trick.|
PG| ***** 1 ***** |


AT|

^B@2^*BMM: ^*NThe above paragraph is really all you need to know. So you can go and do something interesting if you know the above words of wisdom pat. Otherwise keep on reading and keep me off the unemployment roster -:).|
