There is a fairly common situation. Declarer is missing the queen and can finesse either opponent for it. But he has no idea which opponent to finesse. So he will try to have the defense help him by leading an honor from his hand, hoping that an inexperienced defender—not one of us of course—will cover with the queen, thereby eliminating the guess.|PC|h4|
