If West covers the @HJ, South will take all the heart tricks, since West conveniently told him where the @HQ was located. But if West plays low smoothly, most declarers will assume that East must have the @HQ (otherwise West would have at least hesitated). He will therefore win the @HA in dummy and finesse East for the HQ, thereby losing a heart trick that he would  not have lost against a less experienced defender.|
