lb|*CDeclarer led D2 toward the dummy. What card would you play if you were sitting West? Select that card on the right.^^dj^dqj7|SK||NT|^B@2
Here it is advisable, when West is Second Hand, to play for the certainty of making 1 trick. If Declarer leads low you, as West, should play the Jack, which forces the Ace and leaves you with a sure third round winner. Notice carefully the difference between this and the preceding situations. Here the play of the Jack is right because of the threatening Ten in the Dummy.|PC|DJ|
