If Declarer leads the @S6, and you play the Queen, it will hold the trick. But the next time spades are led the Declarer will be able to lead a small card from Dummy and finesse through your Partner's King, rendering it worthless. By playing low on the first trick, you let Partner win with his King while you still retain your Queen as a certain winner for the third round.|PC|S5|
