%% Q 12
st||SK|W|SK|N|md|4dqj9,dk32,da654,dt87|rh||ah|Q 12|ah|Second Hand Play quiz|sv|n|MB|1dPPP|pc|dq|
lb|*CDeclarer led DQ toward the dummy. What card would you play if you were sitting West? Select that card on the right.^^d2^dk32|SK||NT|^B@2
If you, as West, cover with your King, Dummy's Ace will win and then Declarer will lead a low card from this hand. If East plays the eight, Declarer can finesse his nine and catch the Ten with the Jack. |
PG| ***** 284 ***** |


NT|^B@2
Consequently, when you hold the King and the Ten or the nine, you should not hesitate to cover; but without one of these cards, you must weigh the issue. This does not mean that you should fail to cover the Jack if it is led subsequently, for then your only hope is that Partner holds the Ten and that your play of the King will establish a trick.|PC|D2|
pg| ***** 285 ***** |


