lb|*CDeclarer led SJ toward the dummy. What card would you play if you were sitting West? Select that card on the right.^^s7^sq87|SK||NT|^B@2
If Declarer leads the Jack and you cover with the Queen, the Declarer will win with Dummy's Ace and his Ten will now be sitting over Partner's King. If you refuse to cover, Partner will win the trick with the King. Then if the Ten is led later, you can cover and establish Partner's nine.|PC|S7|
